        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Background <S>",
            "relation": "TEXTUAL-ORGANIZATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Surgical site infections ( SSI ) are the commonest healthcare associated infections . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "They severely compromise patient safety ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "are a significant burden on healthcare resources",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "and have an adverse impact on patient quality of life . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "The incidence of SSIs can be as high as 10 % after colorectal procedures . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "The laparoscopic approach is being increasingly used",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "to undertake colorectal procedures . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "It provides advantages over the traditional open approach with smaller incisions , shorter hospital stay and equal oncological outcomes . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "The aim of this meta - analysis was to evaluate whether the laparoscopic approach for colorectal procedures reduces the incidence of SSI",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "compared to the open approach . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Methods <S>",
            "relation": "TEXTUAL-ORGANIZATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Randomised controlled trials ( RCTs )",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "comparing the two approaches",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "published since 2000",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "were included in the review . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Revman 5.3 software was used",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "to carry out the review . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "Data were pooled",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "and the results were shown as risk ratios with 95 % confidence intervals",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 20,
            "text": "using the fixed effects model . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 23,
            "text": "Results <S>",
            "relation": "TEXTUAL-ORGANIZATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "Sixteen RCT 's were included in the analysis",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 24,
            "parent": 23,
            "text": "comprising 5797 patients . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 25,
            "parent": 23,
            "text": "These covered a range of colorectal pathologies",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 26,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "including colon cancer , rectal cancer , inflammatory bowel disease and familial adenomatous polyposis syndrome . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 27,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Analysis showed significantly lower wound infection rates",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 28,
            "parent": 27,
            "text": "( RR : 0.72 , 95 % confidence interval : 0.60 - 0.88 , p = 0.001 )",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 29,
            "parent": 27,
            "text": "and lower abdominal abscess rates",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 30,
            "parent": 29,
            "text": "( RR : 0.88 , 95 % CI 0.62 - 1.27 , p = 0.51 ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 31,
            "parent": 27,
            "text": "The combined SSI rate was significantly lower in laparoscopic",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 32,
            "parent": 31,
            "text": "compared to open surgery",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 33,
            "parent": 32,
            "text": "( RR : 0.76 , 95 % CI 0.64 - 0.90 , p = 0.001 ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 34,
            "parent": 35,
            "text": "Conclusions <S>",
            "relation": "TEXTUAL-ORGANIZATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 35,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Laparoscopic colorectal surgery significantly lowers the incidence of SSI",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 36,
            "parent": 35,
            "text": "compared to open surgery . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        }
    ]
}